The paper proposes a novel approach to using the sequence-to-sequence model for imputing missing sensor data. This involves using a forward and backward RNN to encode the observed data before and after the missing sequence, respectively, and a decoder to predict the missing data. This approach involves deep learning techniques and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the problem of missing sensor data is common in signal processing (cs.SD) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications, making these categories likely as well.
